6 § 4633. FARM AND FORESTRY OPERATIONS SECURITY SPECIAL
7 FUND; GRANTS
8 (a) The Secretary, after consultation with the Review Board, shall award
9 grants from the Farm and Forestry Operations Security Special Fund to farms
10 and forestry operations that have incurred financial losses or expenses due to
11 an eligible weather condition.
12 (1) Grants from the Fund shall be in an amount that reimburses a farm
13 of forestry operation for up to 50 percent of uninsured or otherwise uncovered
14 losses due to eligible weather conditions, up to a maximum award of
15 $150,000.00 total per year per qualified applicant farm or forestry operation.
16 (2) The Secretary shall establish criteria for the amount of an award
17 based on the annual net income of the farm of forestry operation in relation to
18 the median net income of all farms in Vermont.
19 (3) The Secretary may verify the occurrence of an eligible weather
20 condition claimed under this section through use of available data from the
21 National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, from other federal or State
