8 Sec. 3. FUNDING INTENT; REPORT ON FUTURE APPROPRIATIONS
9 (a) It is the intent of the General Assembly that the Farm and Forestry
10 Operations Security Special Fund receive an annual appropriation equal to 50
11 percent of the average documented farm losses from eligible weather
12 conditions, as defined in 6 V.S.A. chapter 207, subchapter 4, averaged over
13 previous years.
14 (b) To determine the appropriate funds for deposit to the Farm and Forestry
15 Operations Security Special Fund, the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and
16 Markets shall recommend to the Farm and Forestry Operations Security
17 Special Fund Review Board on or before December 15, 2025, an amount to be
18 appropriated to the Farm and Forestry Operations Security Special Fund based
19 on the farm losses from eligible weather conditions averaged over the previous
20 three calendar years. On or before January 15, 2026, the Farm and Forestry
21 Operations Security Special Fund Review Board shall submit to the Senate
